Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen I had just had the worst experience at Store #2385 at 409 8th street SE in Washington, D.C. I have already submitted a claim through your app but more has developed.  I placed an order in person only to get home and discover half of my order isn’t in the bag. I called the loaction at 7:17 and spoke to the manager at this location named Fernando Zavala. I told him my issue and that I would like the order refunded to my card. I was told he couldn’t refund my card over the phone and that I had to go to the store for that to be done. Which is another 30 minute round trip. I said on the phone I would be there around 10pm after asking when the location closed and was told 11pm. I get there and I am told not only is he not going to refund me the entire order like he said on the phone but only for the missing items. Fine. He has another associate process a refund then proceeds to attempt to hand me cash back as a refund. I then responded no I want the money back on the card I used as promised on the phone. He then says he can’t do that. He then proceeds to curse me out in Español and said “F**K YOU BUDDY” After telling him I’m not taking cash during a pandemic he says either take the cash or leave. There is literally a sign posted saying to use card or electronic payments because of the pandemic. He then says if you don’t leave I’m calling the police. To be racially profiled as a threat because I’m black after being verbally harassed was the last straw. I said I would gladly call the police for him. The police arrived and asked him if the amount could be refunded to the card. We also both asked if he could make a new transaction to refund to my card, He says no he can not. He then lied to the police and says to them that he told me that he couldn’t process it to my card after two hours when he talked to me over the phone. I had to stop him in his tracks to say if he had told me this on the phone I would have just dealt with the corporate complaint I already filed though the Popeyes App.  This is the worst experience i have ever had at a fast food chain. I don’t have any good reason to go back to another Popeyes if the management are ok treating people this way. I also don’t recommend anyone go to this establishment either.

Leaking pipes, cramped spaces, and an influx of drug induced homeless people are a few of the reasons I keep coming back to this place. To the surprise of nobody with a functioning pallet the food is immaculate, it's like a blue collar brunch. But the atmosphere is why I continue to frequent this joint.  It has character, like no other chain establishment I've ever stepped foot in. The staff handles the homeless hangout with class. All cash register arguments end with a curtain call of compassion. And it's a melting pot of American's making a pilgrimage to enjoy something that unites us... Fast Food  No, these guys in particular are not "Louisiana Fast." But, don't knock the staff for their limited customer service skills, English is a second language for most of them. They're working and trying to earn an honest buck.  Last I checked, the chicken is still fried, the tea is still putting me on a fast track to diabetes, and the sides remind me of real Southern cookin'. There's areas to improve on, but then again, are any of us perfect?
